  <summary date="2021-03-03T19:50:31Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Protecting Individuals with Down Syndrome Act

 This bill creates new federal crimes related to the performance of an abortion on an unborn child who has Down syndrome.

It subjects a violator to criminal penalties&#8212;a fine, a prison term of up to five years, or both.

It also authorizes civil remedies, including damages and injunctive relief.

A woman who undergoes such an abortion may not be prosecuted or held civilly liable.</summary>
